name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On January 17, Hengyang, Hunan. An old lady was carrying a bucket of swill and walking on the road with a boy in dirty clothes.
The photographer said that the grandmother seemed to be blind, and a body was tied around the boy's neck to help him lead the way.
The photographer got off the car and talked to the grandmother, but she was unconscious. A fellow villager revealed that the child's father had died and his mother had remarried. The old lady did not let the child go to school because she was afraid that the child would be abducted.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On January 17, the third session of the 14th Jiangxi Provincial People's Congress opened in Nanchang, but the media broadcasting the event closed the comment section. 
Previously, the Li Yixue incident in Nanchang, Jiangxi, had sparked widespread heated discussions at home and abroad.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: January 18, Baoji, Shaanxi. Construction workers sleep on the floor in the lobby of Xinxiguan Hospital to demand their wages.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
January 18, Tianjin. A merchant disclosed Meituan's double-edged bill. The customer's order amount was 25 yuan. After deducting the commission, delivery fee, and coupons, the merchant actually received more than 6 yuan.
In addition, the customer's end showed that the distance to the merchant was 4.4 kilometers, but the merchant's end showed that the customer was 6.9 kilometers away from the merchant. Meituan charged the merchant a delivery fee based on the distance of 6.9 kilometers, and if the order was not placed, the merchant would be punished by the platform.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: January 18, Zhejiang. A migrant worker who was owed wages stood on a tower crane and shouted at the top of his lungs.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: January 15th, Dalian, Liaoning: Investors of Shanhaihui Group gathered outside the Dalian Intermediate People's Court for several consecutive days to protest their rights.

name: 李老师不是你老师
李老师不是你老师
content:
On January 13, villagers from Xiaohu Village, Zhengzhou, Henan Province, gathered to demand transition fees.
Recently, there have been many cases of demanding transition fees for demolition and resettlement in various parts of Henan Province, and some people's transition fees have even been in arrears for several years.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: January 3, Nantong, Jiangsu Longxiyuan, two months after the property management company forced them to pay for the keys to their properties, which led to a conflict with the owners, Longxiyuan workers blocked the door to demand their wages

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 14, migrant workers in Hainan gathered to demand their wages. The police said: "I understand your feelings, but your behavior of demanding wages is suspected of disturbing the so-called public order. I support you in demanding wages, but you must not take such extreme measures. I understand you, but the public security organs have a bottom line. We cannot say that we can indulge you (demanding wages) even though we know that you are breaking the law." The video was later released by the media as a propaganda of the police's patient persuasion.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
TikTok and CapCut (Cut overseas version) are both banned in the United States.
TikTok's pop-up window shows: Sorry, TikTok is currently unavailable. The United States has enacted a law banning TikTok. Unfortunately, this means you can't use TikTok now. Fortunately, President Trump has said that he will work with us to find a solution to reopen TikTok after he takes office. Stay tuned.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 19, Chifeng, Inner Mongolia. An old man said that he almost lost his eyesight and was a first-level disabled person. In 2017, the government cancelled his subsidy on the grounds of poverty alleviation, making it difficult for him to make a living. After that, he applied for the five-guarantee household, but he has not enjoyed any benefits so far. He reported it to his superiors, and the disability subsidy was also cancelled. The old man said: Where did my targeted poverty alleviation funds go? I beg the leaders to solve it and give me a way out.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On January 17, the owner of Nantong Xiaoniu Kung Fu martial arts hall ran away, and some parents called the police to protect their rights.
The video shows that the wall of the martial arts hall is hung with "Children's education cannot wait", and the title of its Douyin promotional video also reads "A strong youth means a strong country."

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Some Chinese netizens' feelings after checking accounts with the US "TikTok refugees":
"After checking accounts with the US, I found myself turning from pink to deep red"
"Don't let them know how happy we are, or they will go crazy"
"I have seen what capitalism looks like. When I see the Americans crying, I just want to laugh"
"I love my mother even more now. My mother spoils her citizens without saying a word"

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Zhong Haiyan, once a "national advanced worker", also appeared on camera to confess. As a primary school principal, she abused her position to help others with student enrollment, transfers, and class placement, and accepted bribes of 9.49 million yuan.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 16, as the Spring Festival approached, more than a dozen depositors of Henan Village Bank went to Beijing to petition again, demanding that Henan unfreeze their deposits or produce the procedures for freezing their deposits. The depositors endured the severe cold and queued for a whole night.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Taizhou, Jiangsu. Xinghua Middle School did not give students a winter vacation after the final exams, but forced them to continue taking make-up classes, shortening the 26-day winter vacation originally stipulated by the Education Bureau to just over ten days, which triggered protests from students. Finally, the school agreed to a holiday under pressure.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: January 19, Liaoning. A medical worker complained about the poor quality of consumables after the centralized procurement of medical insurance.

January 14th, Taiyuan, Shanxi (based on the license plate in the video) Workers gathered at the door of a government department to demand wages

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On January 18, someone posted a photo of their daughter on Xiaohongshu. An American netizen said: Is this the Chinese middle class? Because the house is very gorgeous.
Chinese netizens said that this is just an ordinary Chinese family, not the middle class.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On January 15, the owners of Pinghu International Import City in Jiaxing, Zhejiang, once again protested against the developer for not fulfilling the ten-year repurchase promise stipulated in the contract. The owners have been protesting for at least a month since December 16.
Some owners posted a video saying that their act of raising the national flag was suppressed. There was also a video saying that more than 12,000 owners were defending their rights, and some owners were arrested in the process of defending their rights.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: After the influx of "TikTok refugees" into Xiaohongshu, a Xiaohongshu employee posted a post complaining about the high intensity of work: "After the layoffs, people were worked to death. I thought I could take a breather before the Chinese New Year, but a "TikTok refugee" came. The department has no manpower and has to complete a lot of requirements. The bosses think that employees are Doraemon and that they can make a wish come true."

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: January 15: Didi Chuxing online car-hailing drivers in Huangshi and Yangxin, Hubei Province, collectively stopped driving and went on strike to protest against low freight rates.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
News Broadcast: In 2024, the GDP will reach 134.9 trillion yuan, an increase of 5.0% over the previous year. What do you think of this report card?
But netizens disagree with the growth: "I have been unemployed for more than a year, and I only eat pickled vegetable buns every day" "I have been unemployed for more than a year, and I only eat two meals a day"

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: According to a report on January 19, the Cyberspace Administration of China will launch a one-month campaign to improve the network environment during the Spring Festival.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Recently, the Shanghai Municipal Committee of the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang stated that patients often report that there are obvious differences in the efficacy of their centralized procurement drugs, which in turn exacerbates patients' resistance to centralized procurement drugs and reduces their trust. 
In addition, the lack of disclosure of efficacy certification information can easily lead to patients' distrust of the quality and efficacy of centralized procurement drugs.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Li Wei'ao, chief reporter of Economic Observer: "Recently, I have met several private entrepreneurs who were caught in deep-sea fishing. The amount of money caught or about to be caught is 60 million, 200 million, and 307 million."

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 18, Chinese people who were going to Russia to join the army posted a video advising people not to come to Russia to join the army: Russian soldiers discriminated against Chinese soldiers, causing many Chinese people to live very depressed after arriving. A while ago, a Chinese person even committed suicide because of this.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
"Soul bargaining" is a waste of time! Gao Xue, director of the National Joint Procurement Office for High-value Medical Consumables, is under investigation.
In the past few years, Gao Xue has served as director of the Procurement Center of Tianjin Medical Insurance Bureau, head of the Procurement Group of the National Joint Procurement Office for High-value Medical Consumables, deputy director of the National Joint Procurement Office for High-value Medical Consumables, and director of the National Joint Procurement Office for High-value Medical Consumables. She is an important operator of the centralized procurement of high-value medical consumables.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
January 19, Yangjiang, Guangdong. A man posted a video saying that his sister Lin Shanshan was lured to his home by the murderer Shi Zhanxiong in 2015 and was killed and dismembered. The court sentenced Shi Zhanxiong to indirect intentional homicide: "He said that the person fell down the stairs and hit her head on the scissors on the shoe rack and died." But the man believed that his sister was premeditated and appealed for help online.
According to the autopsy analysis opinion released by the man: the body parts at the scene can be spliced; no head and neck, bilateral anterior chest soft tissue, sternum and internal organs were found in the body parts at the scene.

content: January 18 (Release), Guangdong. A woman has repeatedly reported medical disputes on the official website of the Bureau of Letters and Calls since November last year, but has not received a response so far, and the official website of the Bureau of Letters and Calls shows that the complaint has been settled.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 19, people logged on to the People's Daily leadership message board to report the problem, and the system showed: Your account has been banned for violating the User Agreement.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 19, Professor Jin Canrong of Renmin University of China forwarded Chen Ping’s inequality: “It is much more comfortable to live with a monthly salary of 2,000 yuan in China than with a monthly salary of 3,000 US dollars in the United States.”

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
January 18 (Released) Hohhot. Blogger interviewed roadside vendor: Did you make money in 2024?
The vendor replied: "I didn't make money last year, and I didn't make money this year. This year is much worse than last year. The income has dropped by at least 2/3, and the consumption capacity of customers has also deteriorated."

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: January 19 (Release), Hubei. An anesthesiologist from a tertiary hospital criticized the Medical Insurance Bureau for its monopoly on power. He said that the current centralized procurement system is completely dominated by the Medical Insurance Bureau. This highly centralized department is actually not subject to checks and balances, and does not face the pressure from the front line - how to treat patients, how to shorten the course of the disease, how to judge the efficacy... He does not understand and is not responsible for it. It only controls the cost. Anyway, it is the hospital and doctors' job to deal with patients.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: January 18, Changchun, Jilin. Blogger "Song Mengya" posted on Weibo that she was forced by her parents to be sent to Changchun Mental Hospital and lost her personal freedom, so she posted a message to seek help from the outside world. "Song Mengya" claimed that she had been controlled by her parents since she was a child, and her parents dominated everything about her, including her major, hobbies, grades, personal life, etc. And friends who wanted to interact with her needed to add her parents' WeChat in advance, resulting in her having no friends for 27 years. Her parents even invited a wizard to come to their home to perform a ritual and forced her to be sent to a mental hospital.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 19, local time, US President-elect Trump posted on social media that he would sign an executive order on Monday to extend the legal deadline before the TikTok ban takes effect. He also said that before the executive order is issued, any company that helps TikTok avoid being shut down will not be held responsible. Trump also said that in order to save TikTok, he hopes to establish a joint venture in which the US side will obtain a 50% stake.
